parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission control module can cause the vehicle to hesitate or jerk while accelerating, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.

the check engine warning light is intermittently illuminated
the vehicle hesitates or jerks while accelerating
the engine revs up and does not accelerate
the vehicle does not shift properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or near-misses.

even when the brakes are applied firmly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to replace defective airbags in a timely manner can leave vehicles in an unsafe condition, putting occupants at risk.

leading to delays and uncertainty about when the issue will be resolved.

symptoms: Sudden loss of brake function
hard brake pedal

vehicle crashes or runs off the road.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system without warning can lead to a loss of control, accidents, and injuries, as the vehicle may not respond to braking inputs, making it difficult or impossible to stop.

hard brake pedal
inability to stop the vehicle
vehicle crashes or runs off the road
